data.text: For 92. 1 Alex. the sabbath-day.the day before the Sabbath, when the land was first inhabited, the praise of a Song by David.
Thy throne is prepared of old: thou art from everlasting.
The rivers have lifted up, O Lord, the rivers have lifted up their voices,92. 3 Alex. + the floods will lift up their waves. See Heb.
at 92. 4 q. d. in answer to.the voices of many waters: the billows of the sea are wonderful: the Lord is wonderful in high places.
Thy testimonies are made very sure: holiness becomes thine house, O Lord, 92. 5 Gr. to length of days.for ever.
